Introduction

CLASS:y is a seven-member project girl group under M25 and Universal Music Japan. The group was formed through the MBC's survival show "My Teenage Girl", which premiered on November 28, 2021. The seven debuting members were announced during the final episode, which was broadcast live on February 27, 2022, and consisted of Won Jimin, Kim Seonyou, Myung Hyungseo, Hong Hyeju, Kim Riwon, Park Boeun, and Yoon Chaewon.

CLASS:y debuted on May 5, 2022, with the mini album "Class Is Over", and the title track "Shut Down".

On June 22, 2022, they made their Japanese debut with the single "Shut Down -JP Ver.-", under Universal Music Japan.
